{
  "message": "fuzz(lrc-repair): 20 structured seeds across LRC config \u00d7 erasure shapes\n\nfuzz_lrc_repair drives ffs_repair::lrc::{encode, repair_local_single,\nrepair_global} through the full LRC parameter space (local_group_size\n\u2208 {2,3,4}, group_count \u2208 1..=4, global_parity_count \u2208 1..=4,\nblock_size \u2208 1..=128) plus erasure-pattern selection and asserts (a)\nencode determinism, (b) local single-block repair recovers exactly,\n(c) global repair recovers when missing \u2264 global_parity, (d) global\nrepair fails when missing > global_parity. Existing 6 ad-hoc seeds\ncovered only basic / a few preset shapes \u2014 never the\n(group_size, group_count, global_parity) corner matrix or block_size\nboundaries.\n\nAdds 20 seeds covering:\n\n  Config matrix:\n  * 2x1 gp1, 3x2 gp1, 4x2 gp2, 2x2 gp1, 3x3 gp3\n  * 4x4 gp4 (largest config)\n  * 2x4 gp2, 3x4 gp3 (max group_count)\n  * 4x2 gp4 (max recoverable count = global_parity)\n\n  Block size boundaries:\n  * b1 (min) for compact seeds\n  * b4, b8 (small payload) \u2014 drives the XOR pattern coverage\n  * b32 (medium payload)\n  * b64 (medium-large payload)\n  * b128 (max \u2014 exercises the largest payload the harness\n    accepts)\n\n  Source data patterns:\n  * default 0x55 fill\n  * all-zero source (0x00) \u2014 exercises encoding of zero\n    payload\n  * all-FF source (0xFF) \u2014 exercises encoding of saturated\n    payload\n  * 0xA5 alternating bit pattern\n\n  Missing-block selection:\n  * first-group / last-group missing block\n  * default (group 0, idx 0) and last (group N-1, idx N-1)\n  * recoverable_count=1 (single missing) and =global_parity\n    (max recoverable)\n\nValidated by an 11 s libFuzzer run: 136k executions over the new\ncorpus, no crashes.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
